solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> memLeak(int memory1, int memory2) {
        long long t = 1;
        while (true) {
            if (memory1 >= memory2) {
                if (memory1 < t) break;
                memory1 -= t;
            } else {
                if (memory2 < t) break;
                memory2 -= t;
            }
            ++t;
        }
        return {(int)t, memory1, memory2};
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(sqrt(memory1 + memory2))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Simulate each second, always subtracting the current second's demand from the larger stick. The loop runs until the demand exceeds both sticks, which happens after roughly sqrt(total memory) iterations.

